+# Hyperclaw
+
+Security-hardened fork of [openclaw](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw) for personal use on a sandboxed Docker work machine.
+
+## Repo layout
+
+```
+origin  → https://github.com/MikeHLee/hyperclaw   (private, our work)
+upstream → https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw    (track for upstream merges)
+
+Branches:
+  main               — stable base, mirrors upstream main
+  upstream-sync      — landing branch for upstream merges, PR → main
+  hyperclaw-security — all our additions, PR → main
+```
+
+To pull upstream changes:
+```bash
+git fetch upstream
+git checkout upstream-sync
+git merge upstream/main
+# resolve conflicts, then open PR → main
+```
+
+## What hyperclaw adds (the `hyperclaw-security` plugin + core patch)
+
+All additions live in `extensions/hyperclaw-security/` **except** one core file patch.
+
+### Core patch (one file)
+- `src/agents/tools/browser-tool.ts` — adds pre-navigate approval gate (mirrors exec approval pattern) at the `navigate` action (~line 614).
+
+### Plugin: `extensions/hyperclaw-security/`
+| Module | Purpose |
+|---|---|
+| `browser-approvals.ts` | URL allowlist + Telegram inline-button approval (mirrors exec-approvals.json format) |
+| `history-logger.ts` | Full agent session log → `~/.openclaw/logs/history/YYYY/MM/DD/<session>.jsonl` |
+| `attack-logger.ts` | Incident stream → `~/.openclaw/logs/attacks/YYYY/MM/DD/<incident>.json` + Telegram alert |
+| `secrets-store.ts` | AES-256-GCM encrypted local vault in `~/.openclaw/state/secrets/` |
+| `tools/report-injection.ts` | Agent self-report tool (inspired by panasonic chat_api `report_user` pattern) |
+| `tools/deposit-secret.ts` | Secrets injection into browser forms — never returns secret to model |
+| `hooks/secrets-redact.ts` | `tool_result_persist` hook — belt-and-suspenders redaction before history write |
+
+### Plugin hook points used
+- `before_prompt_build` — injects security hardening into system prompt
+- `llm_input` / `llm_output` — history logger
+- `before_tool_call` / `after_tool_call` — history logger + attack heuristics
+- `tool_result_persist` — secrets redaction
+- `session_start` / `session_end` — session boundary markers in logs
+
+### Config (in `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`)
+```json
+{
+  "plugins": {
+    "entries": {
+      "hyperclaw-security": {
+        "enabled": true,
+        "telegramAlertChatId": "<your-chat-id>",
+        "secretsKeyDerivation": "gateway-token"
+      }
+    }
+  }
+}
+```
+
+### Approval files
+- `~/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json` — shell command allowlist (existing openclaw)
+- `~/.openclaw/browser-approvals.json` — URL allowlist (hyperclaw addition, same format)
+
+## Inspiration
+- Panasonic chat_api (`~/Documents/Runes/panasonic/sft/dae_pipelines/prod/ecs/chat_api/v1/`):
+  - `report_user` tool → model self-reports detected attacks
+  - `session_logs.py` → dual-stream logging (sessions + incidents)
+  - `agent_loop.py` → tool interception pattern
+
+## Security notes
+- The `deposit_secret` tool NEVER returns the secret value to the model
+- `tool_result_persist` provides belt-and-suspenders redaction of known secret patterns
+- Secrets vault key is PBKDF2-derived from the gateway token (change gateway token = rotate encryption key)
+- Attack logs are write-only from the agent's perspective — the model cannot read them back
